info.description:
This program simulates an interpreter for C++ in that it
allows one to execute individual statements one at a time.
It could be used for quick testing and prototyping.  It is 
built to work on Linux operating systems.  Requires g++ and nano. 
Here is an  example of a possible cppInterpreter session: ::

    C++ : int i;

    C++ : int j;

    C++ : i=1; j=2;

    C++ : cout << i+j;
    3
    C++ : cout << "Hello World!";
    Hello World!
    C++ : int add(int a, int b){
    ... : return a+b;
    ... : }

    C++ : int k = add(2,3);

    C++ : cout << k;
    5
    C++ : 

Contact me to ask questions or give comments on how to improve my code.
